{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"44abeb16-d095-4e2c-bba5-d884d452b8d1","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed *above* them. `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs` but depends on it.\n\nFixing by swapping the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01DMPQs19w7GuzVEUDuC8Pw5","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-c82b5a684c29456cb65fefa64f668ea0/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-c82b5a684c29456cb65fefa64f668ea0/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"6986270d-76dd-42b2-a795-0a45b8de222a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the types\n3. `Program.fs` — uses both\n\nThe fix is to put `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":357,"requestId":"D816:2A9B4:6EAFF2B:76EEA48:6A03CBCB"},"id":"0f8640e2-c9ad-48d9-899c-a648424ee263","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:54:42.581Z","parentId":"71ee18b1-78a6-4ecd-97ce-9db202ae8aee"}
